        <!-- Section for Semantic HTML Tags -->
        <section id="semantic-tags">
            <h2>Semantic HTML Tags</h2>
            <p>Semantic HTML elements provide meaning to the web content. These help search engines and screen readers better understand the structure of your content. Using semantic tags enhances accessibility, SEO, and maintainability.</p>
            
            <h3>Common Semantic Tags</h3>
            <div class="code-box">
                <p>&lt;article&gt; - Represents a self-contained content item, such as a blog post or news article.</p>
                <p>&lt;section&gt; - Defines a section of content, often with a heading.</p>
                <p>&lt;nav&gt; - Defines a section of navigation links.</p>
                <p>&lt;aside&gt; - Represents tangential content, like a sidebar or related links.</p>
                <p>&lt;footer&gt; - Defines the footer content, such as copyright and links.</p>
                <p>&lt;header&gt; - Represents introductory content, typically containing logos and navigation.</p>
            </div>

            <h3>Example:</h3>
            <div class="code-box">
                <p>&lt;article&gt;</p>
                <p>&lt;header&gt;&lt;h1&gt;Article Title&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;/header&gt;</p>
                <p>&lt;section&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Subsection Title&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Content&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/section&gt;</p>
                <p>&lt;footer&gt;Published by Author on Date&lt;/footer&gt;</p>
                <p>&lt;/article&gt;</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section for Forms -->
        <section id="forms">
            <h2>Forms</h2>
            <p>Forms are essential for collecting user data. HTML provides a variety of elements for creating interactive forms.</p>
            
            <h3>Basic Form Elements</h3>
            <div class="code-box">
                <p>&lt;form&gt; - The container for form controls.</p>
                <p>&lt;input&gt; - Used for user input (text, radio buttons, checkboxes, etc.).</p>
                <p>&lt;textarea&gt; - A larger text box for multiline input.</p>
                <p>&lt;select&gt; - Dropdown menu for selecting options.</p>
                <p>&lt;button&gt; - A button that triggers form submission.</p>
            </div>

            <h3>Example Form:</h3>
            <div class="code-box">
                <p>&lt;form action="/submit" method="post"&gt;</p>
                <p>&lt;label for="name"&gt;Name:&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input type="text" id="name" name="name"&gt;</p>
                <p>&lt;label for="email"&gt;Email:&lt;/label&gt;&lt;input type="email" id="email" name="email"&gt;</p>
                <p>&lt;button type="submit"&gt;Submit&lt;/button&gt;</p>
                <p>&lt;/form&gt;</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section for Multimedia -->
        <section id="multimedia">
            <h2>Multimedia</h2>
            <p>Embedding multimedia such as images, videos, and audio enhances user experience. HTML provides easy-to-use tags for multimedia integration.</p>
            
            <h3>Common Multimedia Tags</h3>
            <div class="code-box">
                <p>&lt;img&gt; - Embeds an image. Use alt attribute for accessibility.</p>
                <p>&lt;audio&gt; - Embeds an audio file. Supports controls for playback.</p>
                <p>&lt;video&gt; - Embeds a video file. Can include playback controls and multiple source formats.</p>
            </div>

            <h3>Example:</h3>
            <div class="code-box">
                <p>&lt;img src="image.jpg" alt="A description of the image"&gt;</p>
                <p>&lt;audio controls&gt;&lt;source src="audio.mp3" type="audio/mpeg"&gt;&lt;/audio&gt;</p>
                <p>&lt;video controls&gt;&lt;source src="video.mp4" type="video/mp4"&gt;&lt;/video&gt;</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section for Best Practices -->
        <section id="best-practices">
            <h2>Best Practices</h2>
            <p>Following best practices ensures that your HTML is clean, accessible, and performs well. Here are some tips:</p>
            
            <h3>1. Use Semantic HTML</h3>
            <p>Using semantic tags like <code>&lt;article&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;header&gt;</code>, and <code>&lt;footer&gt;</code> improves SEO and accessibility.</p>

            <h3>2. Ensure Accessibility</h3>
            <p>Use descriptive <code>alt</code> text for images, <code>aria</code> attributes for dynamic content, and proper heading hierarchy.</p>
            
            <h3>3. Validate Your HTML</h3>
            <p>Use the W3C HTML validator to ensure your code is error-free.</p>

            <div class="important">
                <p><strong>Tip:</strong> Always include the <code>&lt;meta charset="UTF-8"&gt;</code> tag in the <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> section to ensure proper character encoding.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

    </main>

